## Channel Management

### Channel Types
- **#channels**: Normal channels (network-wide)
- **&channels**: Local channels (server-specific)
- **+channels**: Modeless channels
- **!channels**: Safe channels (unique IDs)

### Channel Modes
#### User Modes in Channels
```crystal
'o' => "operator"     # Channel operator
'v' => "voice"        # Voice privilege
'h' => "halfop"       # Half-operator (if supported)
```

#### Channel Modes
```crystal
'i' => "invite-only"  # Invite only
'k' => "key"         # Channel key (password)
'l' => "limit"       # User limit
'm' => "moderated"   # Moderated channel
'n' => "no-external" # No external messages
'p' => "private"     # Private channel
's' => "secret"      # Secret channel
't' => "topic-lock"  # Topic lock
'b' => "ban"         # Ban mask
```

### Channel Operations
```crystal
# Join validation
def validate_join(client, channel, key = nil)
  return false if channel.banned?(client.hostmask)
  return false if channel.invite_only? && !channel.invited?(client.nickname)
  return false if channel.has_password? && channel.password != key
  return false if channel.full?
  true
end

# Mode parsing
def parse_mode_string(mode_string)
  adding = true
  modes = [] of {Char, Bool, String?}
  
  mode_string.each_char do |char|
    case char
    when '+'
      adding = true
    when '-'
      adding = false
    else
      modes << {char, adding, nil}
    end
  end
  
  modes
end
```

## Server-to-Server Protocol

### Connection Flow
1. **PASS** - Send password
2. **SERVER** - Send server info
3. **Burst** - Sync initial state
4. **Normal operation** - Forward messages

### Burst Protocol
```crystal
# Send all network state to new server
def send_burst(link_server)
  # Send all servers
  NetworkState.servers.each do |name, server|
    link_server.send_message("SERVER", name, server.hopcount.to_s, server.description)
  end
  
  # Send all users
  NetworkState.users.each do |nick, user|
    link_server.send_message("NICK", nick, user.hopcount.to_s, user.username, 
                             user.hostname, user.server, user.realname)
  end
  
  # Send all channels
  NetworkState.channels.each do |name, channel|
    if channel.members.any?
      nicks = channel.members.keys.join(",")
      link_server.send_message("NJOIN", name, nicks)
    end
  end
end
```

### Message Routing
```crystal
# Route message to appropriate server
def route_message(message, target_server)
  # Find route to target server
  route = NetworkState.route_to_server(target_server)
  
  if route
    # Forward to next hop
    send_to_server(route, message)
  else
    # No route found
    send_error("No route to server")
  end
end
```

## Message Validation

### Parameter Validation
```crystal
def validate_nick(nickname)
  return false if nickname.empty?
  return false if nickname.size > 30
  return false unless nickname.matches?(/^[a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9\-\[\]\\`^{}_]*$/)
  true
end

def validate_channel_name(name)
  return false if name.empty?
  return false unless name.starts_with?('#') || name.starts_with?('&')
  return false if name.size > 200
  return false if name.includes?(' ') || name.includes?('\0') || name.includes?('\r') || name.includes?('\n')
  true
end
```

### Rate Limiting
```crystal
# Implement rate limiting for commands
class RateLimiter
  def initialize(@max_commands = 10, @time_window = 60)
    @command_counts = Hash(String, Array(Time)).new
  end
  
  def check_rate(client_id : String) : Bool
    now = Time.utc
    commands = @command_counts[client_id]? || [] of Time
    
    # Remove old commands outside time window
    commands.reject! { |time| now - time > @time_window.seconds }
    
    if commands.size >= @max_commands
      false
    else
      commands << now
      @command_counts[client_id] = commands
      true
    end
  end
end
```

